#. HTML: <section id="vagga"><section class="sutta" data-uid="an1.41" id="41"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an1.41-50:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 1 "
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 1 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. VAR: sūkavaggo (bj) | paṇihitavagga (pts1)
msgctxt "an1.41-50:0.2"
msgid "5. Paṇihitaacchavagga "
msgstr "5. A Spike "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "an1.41-50:0.3"
msgid "41 "
msgstr "41 "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli1.8, sc41.1
#. VAR: bhecchati → bhejjati (si) | bhijjissati (s1-3, km, mr)
msgctxt "an1.41-50:41.1.1"
msgid "“Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, sālisūkaṃ vā yavasūkaṃ vā micchāpaṇihitaṃ hatthena vā pādena vā akkantaṃ hatthaṃ vā pādaṃ vā bhecchati lohitaṃ vā uppādessatīti netaṃ ṭhānaṃ vijjati. "
msgstr "“Mendicants, suppose a spike of rice or barley was pointing the wrong way. If you trod on it with hand or foot, there’s no way it could break the skin and produce blood. "

msgctxt "an1.41-50:41.1.2"
msgid "Taṃ kissa hetu? "
msgstr "Why is that? "

msgctxt "an1.41-50:41.1.3"
msgid "Micchāpaṇihitattā, bhikkhave, sūkassa. "
msgstr "Because the spike is pointing the wrong way. "

msgctxt "an1.41-50:41.1.4"
msgid "Evamevaṃ kho, bhikkhave, so vata bhikkhu micchāpaṇihitena cittena avijjaṃ bhecchati, vijjaṃ uppādessati, nibbānaṃ sacchikarissatīti netaṃ ṭhānaṃ vijjati. "
msgstr "In the same way, a mendicant whose mind is pointing the wrong way cannot break ignorance, produce knowledge, and realize extinguishment. "

msgctxt "an1.41-50:41.1.5"
msgid "Taṃ kissa hetu? "
msgstr "Why is that? "

msgctxt "an1.41-50:41.1.6"
msgid "Micchāpaṇihitattā, bhikkhave, cittassā”ti. "
msgstr "Because their mind is pointing the wrong way.” "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an1.41-50:41.1.7"
msgid "Paṭhamaṃ. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p></article></section><section class="sutta" data-uid="an1.42" id="42"><article><div class="hgroup"><h1>
msgctxt "an1.41-50:41.1.8"
msgid "42 "
msgstr "42 "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: sc42.1
msgctxt "an1.41-50:42.1.1"
msgid "“Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, sālisūkaṃ vā yavasūkaṃ vā sammāpaṇihitaṃ hatthena vā pādena vā akkantaṃ hatthaṃ vā pādaṃ vā bhecchati lohitaṃ vā uppādessatīti ṭhānametaṃ vijjati. "
msgstr "“Mendicants, suppose a spike of rice or barley was pointing the right way. If you trod on it with hand or foot, it may well break the skin and produce blood. "

msgctxt "an1.41-50:42.1.2"
msgid "Taṃ kissa hetu? "
msgstr "Why is that? "

msgctxt "an1.41-50:42.1.3"
msgid "Sammāpaṇihitattā, bhikkhave, sūkassa. "
msgstr "Because the spike is pointing the right way. "

msgctxt "an1.41-50:42.1.4"
msgid "Evamevaṃ kho, bhikkhave, so vata bhikkhu sammāpaṇihitena cittena avijjaṃ bhecchati, vijjaṃ uppādessati, nibbānaṃ sacchikarissatīti ṭhānametaṃ vijjati. "
msgstr "In the same way, a mendicant whose mind is pointing the right way can break ignorance, produce knowledge, and realize extinguishment. "

msgctxt "an1.41-50:42.1.5"
msgid "Taṃ kissa hetu? "
msgstr "Why is that? "

msgctxt "an1.41-50:42.1.6"
msgid "Sammāpaṇihitattā, bhikkhave, cittassā”ti. "
msgstr "Because the mind is pointing the right way.” "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an1.41-50:42.1.7"
msgid "Dutiyaṃ. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p></article></section><section class="sutta" data-uid="an1.43" id="43"><article><div class="hgroup"><h1>
msgctxt "an1.41-50:42.1.8"
msgid "43 "
msgstr "43 "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: sc43.1
#. VAR: Idhāhaṃ → idāhaṃ (bj)
msgctxt "an1.41-50:43.1.1"
msgid "“Idhāhaṃ, bhikkhave, ekaccaṃ puggalaṃ paduṭṭhacittaṃ evaṃ cetasā ceto paricca pajānāmi: "
msgstr "“Mendicants, when I’ve comprehended the mind of a person whose mind is corrupted, I understand: "

msgctxt "an1.41-50:43.1.2"
msgid "‘imamhi ce ayaṃ samaye puggalo kālaṃ kareyya, yathābhataṃ nikkhitto evaṃ niraye’. "
msgstr "‘If this person were to die right now, they would be cast down to hell.’ "

msgctxt "an1.41-50:43.1.3"
msgid "Taṃ kissa hetu? "
msgstr "Why is that? "

msgctxt "an1.41-50:43.1.4"
msgid "Cittaṃ hissa, bhikkhave, paduṭṭhaṃ. "
msgstr "Because their mind is corrupted. "

msgctxt "an1.41-50:43.1.5"
msgid "Cetopadosahetu pana, bhikkhave, evam’idhekacce sattā kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā apāyaṃ duggatiṃ vinipātaṃ nirayaṃ upapajjantī”ti. "
msgstr "Depravity of mind is the reason why some sentient beings, when their body breaks up, after death, are reborn in a place of loss, a bad place, the underworld, hell.” "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an1.41-50:43.1.6"
msgid "Tatiyaṃ. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p></article></section><section class="sutta" data-uid="an1.44" id="44"><article><div class="hgroup"><h1>
msgctxt "an1.41-50:43.1.7"
msgid "44 "
msgstr "44 "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli1.9, sc44.1
#. VAR: Idhāhaṃ → idāhaṃ (bj)
msgctxt "an1.41-50:44.1.1"
msgid "“Idhāhaṃ, bhikkhave, ekaccaṃ puggalaṃ pasannacittaṃ evaṃ cetasā ceto paricca pajānāmi: "
msgstr "“Mendicants, when I’ve comprehended the mind of a person whose mind is confident, I understand: "

msgctxt "an1.41-50:44.1.2"
msgid "‘imamhi ce ayaṃ samaye puggalo kālaṃ kareyya, yathābhataṃ nikkhitto evaṃ sagge’. "
msgstr "‘If this person were to die right now, they would be raised up to heaven.’ "

msgctxt "an1.41-50:44.1.3"
msgid "Taṃ kissa hetu? "
msgstr "Why is that? "

msgctxt "an1.41-50:44.1.4"
msgid "Cittaṃ hissa, bhikkhave, pasannaṃ. "
msgstr "Because their mind is clear. "

msgctxt "an1.41-50:44.1.5"
msgid "Cetopasādahetu pana, bhikkhave, evam’idhekacce sattā kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā sugatiṃ saggaṃ lokaṃ upapajjantī”ti. "
msgstr "Clarity of mind is the reason why some sentient beings, when their body breaks up, after death, are reborn in a good place, a heavenly realm.” "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an1.41-50:44.1.6"
msgid "Catutthaṃ. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p></article></section><section class="sutta" data-uid="an1.45" id="45"><article><div class="hgroup"><h1>
msgctxt "an1.41-50:44.1.7"
msgid "45 "
msgstr "45 "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: sc45.1
#. VAR: luḷito → lulito (bj, s1-3)
#. VAR: sippisambukampi → sippikasambukampi (mr)
msgctxt "an1.41-50:45.1.1"
msgid "“Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, udakarahado āvilo luḷito kalalībhūto tattha cakkhumā puriso tīre ṭhito na passeyya sippisambukampi sakkharakaṭhalampi macchagumbampi carantampi tiṭṭhantampi. "
msgstr "“Suppose, mendicants, there was a lake that was cloudy, murky, and muddy. A person with good eyesight standing on the bank would not see the mussel shells, gravel and pebbles, and schools of fish swimming about or staying still. "

msgctxt "an1.41-50:45.1.2"
msgid "Taṃ kissa hetu? "
msgstr "Why is that? "

msgctxt "an1.41-50:45.1.3"
msgid "Āvilattā, bhikkhave, udakassa. "
msgstr "Because the water is clouded. "

msgctxt "an1.41-50:45.1.4"
msgid "Evamevaṃ kho, bhikkhave, so vata bhikkhu āvilena cittena attatthaṃ vā ñassati paratthaṃ vā ñassati ubhayatthaṃ vā ñassati uttariṃ vā manussadhammā alamariyañāṇadassanavisesaṃ sacchikarissatīti netaṃ ṭhānaṃ vijjati. "
msgstr "In the same way, that a mendicant whose mind is clouded would know what’s for their own good, the good of another, or the good of both; or that they would realize any superhuman distinction in knowledge and vision worthy of the noble ones: this is not possible. "

msgctxt "an1.41-50:45.1.5"
msgid "Taṃ kissa hetu? "
msgstr "Why is that? "

msgctxt "an1.41-50:45.1.6"
msgid "Āvilattā, bhikkhave, cittassā”ti. "
msgstr "Because their mind is clouded.” "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an1.41-50:45.1.7"
msgid "Pañcamaṃ. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p></article></section><section class="sutta" data-uid="an1.46" id="46"><article><div class="hgroup"><h1>
msgctxt "an1.41-50:45.1.8"
msgid "46 "
msgstr "46 "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: sc46.1
msgctxt "an1.41-50:46.1.1"
msgid "“Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, udakarahado accho vippasanno anāvilo tattha cakkhumā puriso tīre ṭhito passeyya sippisambukampi sakkharakaṭhalampi macchagumbampi carantampi tiṭṭhantampi. "
msgstr "“Suppose, mendicants, there was a lake that was transparent, clear, and unclouded. A person with good eyesight standing on the bank would see the mussel shells, gravel and pebbles, and schools of fish swimming about or staying still. "

msgctxt "an1.41-50:46.1.2"
msgid "Taṃ kissa hetu? "
msgstr "Why is that? "

msgctxt "an1.41-50:46.1.3"
msgid "Anāvilattā, bhikkhave, udakassa. "
msgstr "Because the water is unclouded. "

msgctxt "an1.41-50:46.1.4"
msgid "Evamevaṃ kho, bhikkhave, so vata bhikkhu anāvilena cittena attatthaṃ vā ñassati paratthaṃ vā ñassati ubhayatthaṃ vā ñassati uttariṃ vā manussadhammā alamariyañāṇadassanavisesaṃ sacchikarissatīti ṭhānametaṃ vijjati. "
msgstr "In the same way, that a mendicant whose mind is not clouded would know what’s for their own good, the good of another, or the good of both; or that they would realize any superhuman distinction in knowledge and vision worthy of the noble ones: this is possible. "

msgctxt "an1.41-50:46.1.5"
msgid "Taṃ kissa hetu? "
msgstr "Why is that? "

msgctxt "an1.41-50:46.1.6"
msgid "Anāvilattā, bhikkhave, cittassā”ti. "
msgstr "Because their mind is unclouded.” "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an1.41-50:46.1.7"
msgid "Chaṭṭhaṃ. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p></article></section><section class="sutta" data-uid="an1.47" id="47"><article><div class="hgroup"><h1>
msgctxt "an1.41-50:46.1.8"
msgid "47 "
msgstr "47 "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: sc47.1
msgctxt "an1.41-50:47.1.1"
msgid "“Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, yāni kānici rukkhajātānaṃ phandano tesaṃ aggamakkhāyati yadidaṃ mudutāya ceva kammaññatāya ca. "
msgstr "“Just as, mendicants, the <i>papra</i> is said to be the best kind of tree in terms of its pliability and workability, "

msgctxt "an1.41-50:47.1.2"
msgid "Evamevaṃ kho ahaṃ, bhikkhave, nāññaṃ ekadhammampi samanupassāmi yaṃ evaṃ bhāvitaṃ bahulīkataṃ mudu ca hoti kammaññañca yathayidaṃ cittaṃ. "
msgstr "so too, I do not see a single thing that’s as pliable and workable as the mind, when it is developed and cultivated. "

msgctxt "an1.41-50:47.1.3"
msgid "Cittaṃ, bhikkhave, bhāvitaṃ bahulīkataṃ mudu ca hoti kammaññañca hotī”ti. "
msgstr "A mind that is developed and cultivated is pliable and workable.” "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an1.41-50:47.1.4"
msgid "Sattamaṃ. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p></article></section><section class="sutta" data-uid="an1.48" id="48"><article><div class="hgroup"><h1>
msgctxt "an1.41-50:47.1.5"
msgid "48 "
msgstr "48 "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli1.10, sc48.1
msgctxt "an1.41-50:48.1.1"
msgid "“Nāhaṃ, bhikkhave, aññaṃ ekadhammampi samanupassāmi yaṃ evaṃ lahuparivattaṃ yathayidaṃ cittaṃ. "
msgstr "“Mendicants, I do not see a single thing that’s as quick to change as the mind. "

msgctxt "an1.41-50:48.1.2"
msgid "Yāvañcidaṃ, bhikkhave, upamāpi na sukarā yāva lahuparivattaṃ cittan”ti. "
msgstr "So much so that it’s not easy to give a simile for how quickly the mind changes.” "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an1.41-50:48.1.3"
msgid "Aṭṭhamaṃ. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p></article></section><section class="sutta" data-uid="an1.49" id="49"><article><div class="hgroup"><h1>
msgctxt "an1.41-50:48.1.4"
msgid "49 "
msgstr "49 "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: sc49.1
msgctxt "an1.41-50:49.1.1"
msgid "“Pabhassaramidaṃ, bhikkhave, cittaṃ. "
msgstr "“This mind, mendicants, is radiant. "

msgctxt "an1.41-50:49.1.2"
msgid "Tañca kho āgantukehi upakkilesehi upakkiliṭṭhan”ti. "
msgstr "But it’s corrupted by passing corruptions.” "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an1.41-50:49.1.3"
msgid "Navamaṃ. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p></article></section><section class="sutta" data-uid="an1.50" id="50"><article><div class="hgroup"><h1>
msgctxt "an1.41-50:49.1.4"
msgid "50 "
msgstr "50 "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: sc50.1
msgctxt "an1.41-50:50.1.1"
msgid "“Pabhassaramidaṃ, bhikkhave, cittaṃ. "
msgstr "“This mind, mendicants, is radiant. "

msgctxt "an1.41-50:50.1.2"
msgid "Tañca kho āgantukehi upakkilesehi vippamuttan”ti. "
msgstr "And it is freed from passing corruptions.” "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an1.41-50:50.1.3"
msgid "Dasamaṃ. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an1.41-50:50.1.4"
msgid "Paṇihitaacchavaggo pañcamo. "
msgstr ""

#. HTML: </p></article></section></section></body></html>
